# EduOffline Smart - Software Requirements Specification (SRS)

## 1. Introduction

### Purpose
EduOffline Smart is a mobile application that allows students living in areas with limited or no internet access to continue learning offline.

### Target Users
- Primary school students
- Middle school students
- High school students
- Teachers
- NGOs
- Educational organizations

## 2. Functional Requirements

The application shall allow users to:

- Create an account
- Log in
- Download courses
- Access downloaded courses offline
- Watch educational videos offline
- Read PDF lessons
- Complete quizzes
- Track learning progress
- Synchronize data automatically when internet is available

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

- Fast performance
- Secure authentication
- Offline-first architecture
- Data encryption
- Easy-to-use interface
- Multi-language support